    "It demonstrates that the dimensions of the input and output images are the same.",
    "If the same procedure is done without padding, the output might have a smaller-sized image.",
    "Consequently, a 5 × 5 × 1 image will be converted to a 3 × 3 × 1 image (Bhatt et al. 2021).",
    "Upon acquiring the feature maps, a pooling (down sampling) layer must be added.",
    "The neurons in the pooling layer are connected to the local receptive domains of their input layer, i.e., the convolution layer, and the local receptive domains of different neurons do not overlap."
